Interface Assigner<DATATYPE>

  • Type Parameters:
    DATATYPE - the primitive array datatype which represents a centroid of this cluster.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    HardAssigner<DATATYPE,DISTANCES,DISTANCE_INDEX>, SoftAssigner<DATATYPE,DISTANCES>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ByteKNNAssigner, ClusterLimitedIntRAC, ConstrainedFloatAssigner, DoubleKNNAssigner, ExactByteAssigner, ExactDoubleAssigner, ExactFeatureVectorAssigner, ExactFloatAssigner, ExactIntAssigner, ExactLongAssigner, ExactShortAssigner, FloatKNNAssigner, HierarchicalByteHardAssigner, HierarchicalBytePathAssigner, HierarchicalDoubleHardAssigner, HierarchicalDoublePathAssigner, HierarchicalFloatHardAssigner, HierarchicalFloatPathAssigner, HierarchicalIntHardAssigner, HierarchicalIntPathAssigner, HierarchicalLongHardAssigner, HierarchicalLongPathAssigner, HierarchicalShortHardAssigner, HierarchicalShortPathAssigner, IntKNNAssigner, IntRAC, IntRandomForest, KDTreeByteEuclideanAssigner, KDTreeDoubleEuclideanAssigner, KDTreeFloatEuclideanAssigner, KDTreeIntEuclideanAssigner, KDTreeLongEuclideanAssigner, KDTreeShortEuclideanAssigner, LongKNNAssigner, ShortKNNAssigner

    public interface Assigner<DATATYPE>
    Super interface for all assigners. Assigners take a point and assign it to cluster(s).

    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
